.entry-header
About Us
Hurricane Eddie's was born January 11th, 2017,
after a fire destroyed the formally iconic
"Inn"
on Dunedin Causeway.
How did we get our name? It started with a contest! We wanted to incorporate the name of our sister location, Eddie's Bar & Grill.  What better way to come up with a name...than to let our customers be a part of the process. We value our customers, so it seemed right to include them in naming our new location. We had so many great names submitted. Once they were submited we narrowed it down to the top entries and then our facebook followers voted on the name. Hurricane Eddie's was the clear winner.  The person that suggested the name received
free drinks an entire year!
Now Hurricane Eddie's is not just the most popular place on Dunedin Causeway, but we have expanded. We now have four locations to serve you, Dunedin,
Clearwater Beach, Indian Rocks Beach,
and Gulfport.
All are full liquor local beach bars, with pool tables, darts, games, and plenty of tv's to watch your
favorite sports teams.
You'll find our customers and our staff friendly & welcoming at all of our locations.
We offer a fun atmosphere
with the feel
of the laid back
Florida lifestyle we all enjoy!
People and pet friendly.
Good Vibes & Good Times
.entry-content .clear
